Simulating a Disruption (Demo Mode)
GigShield includes a demo trigger API for live demonstrations:
bash# Simulate a Heavy Rain event in Tambaram zone
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/demo/trigger \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <admin_token>" \
  -d '{
    "trigger_id": "T-01",
    "zone_pincode": "600045",
    "zone_name": "Tambaram, Chennai",
    "intensity": "red_alert",
    "duration_hours": 3
  }'

# Expected response:
# {
#   "trigger_event_id": "EVT-xxxxx",
#   "affected_workers": 42,
#   "claims_initiated": 38,
#   "claims_auto_approved": 35,
#   "claims_in_review": 3,
#   "total_payout_queued": "₹6,840",
#   "estimated_completion": "8 minutes"
# }
You can watch the claims flow through in real-time on the insurer dashboard.

